One person was killed, and many others were injured after a
bus rolled down an embankment on the R66 in Gingindlovu, KwaZulu-Natal, on
Saturday morning. Arrive Alive reported that IPSS Medical Rescue was currently
on scene on the R66 between Gingindlovu and Eshowe, where a bus left the
roadway and rolled down an embankment, resulting in multiple injuries. When IPSS Search and Rescue technicians accessed the bus,
they found that approximately 50 people were injured. Sadly, one person had died
at the scene. This is a developing story. 